        "id": 3305531,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-12-31T01:23:55.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Given the exigence of C\u00e9dric\u2019s viticulture, it would be a mistake to discount his 2017s on the basis of generalizations about the vintage.</p>\n<p>What\u2019s more, remember, Bouchard is only 1 hour drive from Chablis; he\u2019s 1h30 from Mesnil-sur-Oger. By all accounts, 2017 Chablis wasn\u2019t so bad\u2026</p>",
